sentences.english: But the OECD figure is quite different to the official Chinese figures.
sentences.chinese: 但是經合組織的數字與中國官方的統計數據迥異。

sentences.english: The organisation has now broken out numbers on wireless broadband subscriptions.
sentences.chinese: 目前經合組織統計出了無線寬帶用戶的數量。

sentences.english: Regional organizations such as APEC have already shown considerable progress in these areas.
sentences.chinese: 亞太經合組織等地區組織已在這些領域取得可觀進展。

sentences.english: He also chaired the editorial board of OECD Economic Studies.
sentences.chinese: 他同時擔任“經合組織經濟學研究”編委會主席。

sentences.english: U.S. President George Bush is in Peru for his final Pacific Rim summit.
sentences.chinese: 美國總統布什前往祕魯出席亞太經合組織高峯會。

sentences.english: E. C. D. countries that the number of nurses is too small toresponserespond to the demand.
sentences.chinese: 大多數經合組織成員國擔心護士短缺無法滿足需求。

sentences.english: The Chinese Statistical Bureau provides data more easily than the OECD.
sentences.chinese: 中國國家統計局比經合組織更容易提供數據。

sentences.english: There are concerns in most O. E. C. D. countries that the number of nurses is too small to respond to the demand.
sentences.chinese: 大多數經合組織成員國擔心護士太少會無法滿足需求。

sentences.english: The transfer of one partys share in the registered capital shall be effected only with the consent of the other parties to the venture.
sentences.chinese: 合營者的註冊資本如果轉讓必須經合營各方同意。

sentences.english: A representative for the Mainland Affairs Council said that the CSECC will meet twice a year.
sentences.chinese: 陸委會代表表示兩岸經合會每年將召開兩次會議。

sentences.english: Thomas Liebig is the an economist in at the OECD.
sentences.chinese: 托馬斯李比希是經合組織的一名經濟學家。

sentences.english: The 30-nation OECD brings together nations committed to democracy and a free-market economy.
sentences.chinese: 經合組織由致力於民主和自由市場經濟的30國組成。

sentences.english: By contrast, Asian OECD countries Japan and South Korea are the leanest.
sentences.chinese: 相比之下，經合組織的亞洲成員國日本和韓國最瘦。
